headline: Qualcomm Weighs Handset Setback Against AI And Automotive Opportunities
summary: Qualcomm, NasdaqGS:QCOM, is seeing near term disruption in its core smartphone business as an industry wide memory chip shortage constrains handset production. Multiple OEMs, particularly in China, are scaling back device output, leading Qualcomm to issue cautious guidance on handset chip demand. In response, the company is leaning into diversification with recent moves in data centers, RISC V CPUs, automotive partnerships, and new AI, IoT, and robotics products.
